    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Cut the<strong>&nbsp;red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon)</p> <p>Cut the<strong> tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into wedges, then crush the <strong>garlic</strong> with the side of a knife and peel off the skin</p> <p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;pepper</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong> and <strong>peeled garlic</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>, then<strong>&nbsp;</strong>put in the oven for 20 min until softened&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle&nbsp;</p> <p>Chop the <strong>waxy</strong>&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a pot with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p> <p>Cover the potatoes with <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a medium heat for 10-15 min or until tender</p> <p>Once they're cooked, drain return them to the pot to steam dry&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with of a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork tenderloin</strong> and cook on all sides for 1-2 min or until lightly browned (this is known as searing)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> seared pork tenderloin</strong> and <strong>T</strong><strong>enderstem broccoli</strong>&nbsp;to your baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;(keep the pan and the pork juices for step 7!)</p> <p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until the <strong>pork</strong> is cooked through and the<strong>&nbsp;Tenderstem broccoli&nbsp;</strong>is&nbsp;tender</p> <p>Once done,&nbsp;transfer the <strong>pork</strong> to a chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel to rest&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>red&nbsp;pepper</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> has softened, transfer them to a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar </strong>and grind&nbsp;everything to&nbsp;a coarse paste</p> <p>Tip: if you don't have a pestle and mortar, chop everything very finely or use a food processor&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ground red pepper</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to a medium bowl with the <strong>ground almonds</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>smoked paprika</strong>&nbsp;</p> <p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>,&nbsp;a generous pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up - this is your <strong>romesco sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved&nbsp;pan to a high heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p> <p>Once melted, add the drained<strong> potatoes</strong> and a generous pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Lightly crush them with a masher or fork, being careful not to mash them&nbsp;fully and cook for 3-5 min or until they're just starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-romesco-sauce-and-tenderstem/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> crushed potatoes</strong> alongside the<strong>&nbsp;Tenderstem broccoli</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>romesco sauce</strong></p> <p>Slice the rested<strong>&nbsp;pork&nbsp;</strong>and serve it over the<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>romesco sauce&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
